# Auto Scaling (ASG)

## Overview
Auto Scaling automatically adjusts the number of EC2 instances based on demand.
---

## Key Concepts

### Auto Scaling Group (ASG)
- Group of EC2 instances
- Maintains desired number of instances

### Scaling Policies

#### 1. Dynamic Scaling
- Based on metrics (CPU, traffic)

#### 2. Scheduled Scaling
- Scale at specific times
---

## Example
If CPU > 70%:
→ Add more instances
If CPU < 30%:
→ Remove instances
---

## Benefits
- Cost efficiency
- High availability
- Automatic scaling
 
